title: Refine tracklets Attributeerror
body:
### Is there an existing issue for this?

- [X] I have searched the existing issues

### Bug description

While refining tracklets, when I click on individual 1 to swap the labels for individual 1 and 2, I get an attributeerror in the terminal. 

![Figure_1](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/47169385/152520014-8e0d9e76-78ef-40e3-93b7-6a00245c25ba.png)
1

(base) csbd@csbd-System-Product-Name:~$ conda activate DEEPLABCUT
(DEEPLABCUT) csbd@csbd-System-Product-Name:~$ python -m deeplabcut
/home/csbd/anaconda3/envs/DEEPLABCUT/lib/python3.8/site-packages/statsmodels/compat/pandas.py:65: FutureWarning: pandas.Int64Index is deprecated and will be removed from pandas in a future version. Use pandas.Index with the appropriate dtype instead.
  from pandas import Int64Index as NumericIndex
Starting GUI...
Traceback (most recent call last):
  File "/home/csbd/anaconda3/envs/DEEPLABCUT/lib/python3.8/site-packages/matplotlib/cbook/__init__.py", line 287, in process
    func(*args, **kwargs)
  File "/home/csbd/anaconda3/envs/DEEPLABCUT/lib/python3.8/site-packages/deeplabcut/gui/tracklet_toolbox.py", line 511, in on_pick
    self.ax_slider.lines = []
AttributeError: can't set attribute


### Operating System

ubuntu20.04



### DeepLabCut version

dlc version latest version (2.0.6)

### DeepLabCut mode

multi animal

### Device type

I want to use the gpu (gpu 3090), but seems like I'm using the cpu.

### Steps To Reproduce

(DEEPLABCUT) csbd@csbd-System-Product-Name:~$ conda list
